22/11/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The second meeting of the EU-Western Balkans foreign ministers' forum opens Monday (22 November) in Brussels.
Participating in the event are representatives of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Macedonia, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro and Turkey, as well as representatives of the EU and the Stability Pact.
They will discuss relations between the EU and the Western Balkans, the impact of the recent EU expansion, and regional developments.
Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic is expected to sign an agreement on the basic principles of Serbia-Montenegro's participation in EU programmes.
(Beta - 22/11/04;
Tanjug, HINA, ATA - 21/11/04)
